SOPHOMORE (2023-24)

• 2023-24 AAC All-Academic Team

• Scored 39 points at the AAC Championships, plus another 66 in relay events

• Competed in the 200 Breast and the 200 IM at the CSCAA National Invitational, finishing 45th in both events

• Competed in 11 meets on the season, recording six top-three finishes

FRESHMAN (2022-2023)

• Conference USA Academic Honor Roll

• Scored 58 points at the AAC Championships, placing fifth in the 200 IM, 10th in the 200 Breast, and 11th in the 400 IM

• Scored 16 points at the CSCAA National Invitational with a fifth-place finish in the400 IM, setting a personal best.

Prior to Rice

Swam for coach Gunnar Schmidt (Club Wolverine) and Stef Kerska at Pioneer High School... finished first in the 200 free and second in the 100 breast at the 2021 state meet.... Finished ninth in the 100 breast at Speedo Winter Junior Nationals East in 2021.

Personal

Born: October 15 in Livonia, Michigan... Parents: Jess and Johanna Cramer... one brother, one sister... Father played lacrosse at Texas Tech for 4 years and sister (Emma Brann) played volleyball at Olivet College for 4 years.
